<post author="wollery" datetime="2012-02-27T15:08:00" id="p17">
Explaining the nanosecond to someone who doesn't already know what a nanosecond is, and isn't in a 10th grade science class specifically to learn about it :-

"It's a very, very short period of time. Much shorter than you will ever care to think about, and incredibly shorter than you will ever need to measure."
</post>
